WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.840 --> 00:00:05.314
Prof: Okay,
this is the final lecture on

00:00:05.314 --> 00:00:06.750
electromagnetism.
 

00:00:06.750 --> 00:00:11.293
When you come back from the
break we will start doing

00:00:11.293 --> 00:00:12.080
optics.
 

00:00:12.080 --> 00:00:15.250
Of course you know by now
that's really electromagnetism,

00:00:15.250 --> 00:00:19.094
but it's going to be somewhat
easier on your imagination

00:00:19.094 --> 00:00:22.660
because it doesn't involve many
abstract things,

00:00:22.660 --> 00:00:24.950
pretty concrete things.
 

00:00:24.950 --> 00:00:28.434
Then it'll take a turn for the
worse when we do quantum

00:00:28.434 --> 00:00:31.983
mechanics, but I think the
mathematics of that should be

00:00:31.983 --> 00:00:33.080
quite simple.
 

00:00:33.080 --> 00:00:36.179
Before you do that you should
make sure you know all about

00:00:36.179 --> 00:00:39.333
elementary complex numbers like
what is e^(i)

00:00:39.333 --> 00:00:40.530
^(θ).
 

00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:42.850
You should get that completely
into your system.

00:00:42.850 --> 00:00:46.902
It's going to be all about
that, then very elementary

00:00:46.902 --> 00:00:49.240
calculus, just one variable.
 

00:00:49.240 --> 00:00:53.490
So last time I told you that if
you want to solve Maxwell's

00:00:53.490 --> 00:00:58.033
equation in free space you can
write down any function you want

00:00:58.033 --> 00:01:00.564
for
E and B that

00:01:00.564 --> 00:01:03.259
satisfy the four Maxwell
equations.

00:01:03.259 --> 00:01:08.253
Two involve surface integrals,
and two involve line integrals,

00:01:08.253 --> 00:01:11.610
and the answer we got looked
like this.

00:01:11.610 --> 00:01:16.510
This is x,
y and z.

00:01:16.510 --> 00:01:19.069
The electric field is going to
point that way,

00:01:19.069 --> 00:01:21.269
magnetic field is going to
point that way,

00:01:21.269 --> 00:01:25.653
and the functional form E
was k (k is

00:01:25.653 --> 00:01:28.498
unit vector in the z
direction)

00:01:28.498 --> 00:01:32.420
E_0sin(ky -
ωt),

00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:41.712
and B was
iB_0sin(ky -

00:01:41.712 --> 00:01:44.810
ωt).
 

00:01:44.810 --> 00:01:48.827
When you take this assumed form
with this y and this

00:01:48.827 --> 00:01:51.390
t dependence you will
find,

00:01:51.390 --> 00:01:55.080
as written, they automatically
satisfy the surface integral,

00:01:55.080 --> 00:01:58.777
and the surface integral of
these fields on any tiny cube

00:01:58.777 --> 00:01:59.569
will be 0.
 

00:01:59.569 --> 00:02:03.108
When you do line integrals you
can take a loop in this plane,

00:02:03.108 --> 00:02:04.430
and that plane,
and the third plane,

00:02:04.430 --> 00:02:07.174
and you fool around you get
some additional constraints

00:02:07.174 --> 00:02:09.482
which I derived,
but I don't want to do that

00:02:09.482 --> 00:02:09.830
again.
 

00:02:09.830 --> 00:02:14.495
But the conditions you derive
are that ω should

00:02:14.495 --> 00:02:17.580
be equal to k times
c,

00:02:17.580 --> 00:02:23.180
and remember the velocity of
light emerged at this following

00:02:23.180 --> 00:02:24.508
combination.
 

00:02:24.508 --> 00:02:29.470
Then you will find the magnetic
field should be electric field

00:02:29.470 --> 00:02:31.258
divided by c.
 

00:02:31.258 --> 00:02:35.853
These are the two conditions
you get from writing the two

00:02:35.853 --> 00:02:36.508
other.
 

00:02:36.508 --> 00:02:37.960
There are three equations for
loops.

00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:41.021
One of them is trivially
satisfied 0 = 0,

00:02:41.021 --> 00:02:43.090
the others give you this.
 

00:02:43.090 --> 00:02:47.430
Now I want you to be able to at
least visualize these fields.

00:02:47.430 --> 00:02:49.750
You can write them on a piece
of paper, but E is not

00:02:49.750 --> 00:02:50.628
the letter E.
 

00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:53.120
E stands for something
physical.

00:02:53.120 --> 00:02:55.610
So what do these things do?
 

00:02:55.610 --> 00:02:59.288
First of all what is k
and what is ω?

00:02:59.288 --> 00:03:02.637
I realize that some of you are
not familiar with what k

00:03:02.637 --> 00:03:03.680
and ω mean.
 

00:03:03.680 --> 00:03:07.189
First of all you know it's a
periodic function in y at

00:03:07.189 --> 00:03:08.770
fixed t,
if you like,

00:03:08.770 --> 00:03:11.169
because sine of anything is
periodic.

00:03:11.169 --> 00:03:15.515
That means at a given time if
you take a snapshot of this

00:03:15.515 --> 00:03:19.199
E it'll be oscillating as
you vary y.

00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:22.401
And at a given point in space,
if you study it as a function

00:03:22.401 --> 00:03:25.131
of time,
it'll be also oscillating in

00:03:25.131 --> 00:03:28.710
time with an angular frequency
ω.

00:03:28.710 --> 00:03:32.342
So let me relate these
quantities to more familiar

00:03:32.342 --> 00:03:33.008
things.
 

00:03:33.008 --> 00:03:38.764
If the wave looks like this,
and E is going to point

00:03:38.764 --> 00:03:42.518
in that direction,
you know that if you go a full

00:03:42.518 --> 00:03:44.910
wavelength you come back to
where you are.

00:03:44.910 --> 00:03:47.050
So let's call the wavelength
λ.

00:03:47.050 --> 00:03:50.834
It's clear then whatever
happens at 0 happens at

00:03:50.834 --> 00:03:51.720
λ.
 

00:03:51.720 --> 00:03:54.375
At zero, ky is 0,
at λ,

00:03:54.375 --> 00:03:56.440
ky should be 2Π.
 

00:03:56.440 --> 00:04:01.824
When you go a distance lambda
it should be equal to a 2Π

00:04:01.824 --> 00:04:02.658
change.
 

00:04:02.658 --> 00:04:06.270
So λ,
which is more familiar to you

00:04:06.270 --> 00:04:10.232
as the wavelength,
is the reciprocal up to the

00:04:10.232 --> 00:04:13.490
factor of 2Π
of this k.

00:04:13.490 --> 00:04:18.439
k is called the wave
number.

00:04:18.439 --> 00:04:22.483
The bigger the k the
more rapidly the wave

00:04:22.483 --> 00:04:23.579
oscillates.
 

00:04:23.579 --> 00:04:28.033
That is bigger the λ
the long wavelength means more

00:04:28.033 --> 00:04:30.300
slowly the wave oscillates.
 

00:04:30.300 --> 00:04:34.851
Similarly you can come to the
second guy and you can ask

00:04:34.851 --> 00:04:37.170
yourself--let me continue.
 

00:04:37.170 --> 00:04:38.819
So that's what E is.
 

00:04:38.819 --> 00:04:41.471
B, again,
is a function of space at a

00:04:41.471 --> 00:04:44.420
given time if you draw it,
but the B vector's

00:04:44.420 --> 00:04:50.401
pointing this way,
so it'll look like this,

00:04:50.401 --> 00:04:57.350
and you can keep repeating
this.

00:04:57.350 --> 00:04:58.870
So E is going back.
 

00:04:58.870 --> 00:05:01.290
So now this is the thing to
understand with this graph.

00:05:01.290 --> 00:05:04.064
You can see this graph,
but you should know what it

00:05:04.064 --> 00:05:04.509
means.
 

00:05:04.509 --> 00:05:09.894
This whole graph describes the
situation at one given time only

00:05:09.894 --> 00:05:12.759
at points on the y-axis.
 

00:05:12.759 --> 00:05:16.050
I've drawn it only at points on
the y-axis.

00:05:16.050 --> 00:05:17.800
So this arrow,
even though it sticks out here

00:05:17.800 --> 00:05:19.750
and there, is not talking about
a whole region.

00:05:19.750 --> 00:05:22.300
It's talking about that one
point.

00:05:22.300 --> 00:05:24.550
For example,
at this one point the electric

00:05:24.550 --> 00:05:27.069
field points this way and has
that magnitude.

00:05:27.069 --> 00:05:30.202
At this point the electric
field points down and has that

00:05:30.202 --> 00:05:32.180
magnitude,
and the magnetic field points

00:05:32.180 --> 00:05:34.432
away from the board,
here the magnetic field into

00:05:34.432 --> 00:05:36.110
the board and away from the
board,

00:05:36.110 --> 00:05:37.319
okay?
 

00:05:37.319 --> 00:05:40.690
That's the situation at one
time.

00:05:40.690 --> 00:05:44.529
Then you can ask yourself what
happens later.

00:05:44.529 --> 00:05:45.779
You can do it in two ways.
 

00:05:45.779 --> 00:05:48.055
First of all let me tell you
the relation between

00:05:48.055 --> 00:05:49.810
ω and the time
period.

00:05:49.810 --> 00:05:53.244
If you wait a full time period
everything should come back to

00:05:53.244 --> 00:05:55.704
where it was,
so the time period T by

00:05:55.704 --> 00:05:57.879
definition will be this
condition.

00:05:57.879 --> 00:06:04.088
Therefore, the time period that
you guys are all familiar with

00:06:04.088 --> 00:06:08.668
is also related to
ω by a similar

00:06:08.668 --> 00:06:09.889
formula.
 

00:06:09.889 --> 00:06:15.420
So one way to write this wave
that is in terms of things

00:06:15.420 --> 00:06:20.853
you're more familiar with would
be to say it looks like

00:06:20.853 --> 00:06:25.077
E_0
sin(2Πy/λ

00:06:25.077 --> 00:06:27.290
- 2Πt/T).
 

00:06:27.290 --> 00:06:30.242
This is completely equivalent
to what I wrote because these

00:06:30.242 --> 00:06:32.891
are the definitions of
ω and k in

00:06:32.891 --> 00:06:35.029
terms of λ and
T.

00:06:35.029 --> 00:06:38.202
Maybe writing it this way is
more transparent - that if you

00:06:38.202 --> 00:06:40.829
add a λ
to y on the top,

00:06:40.829 --> 00:06:43.218
if you say y goes to
y λ

00:06:43.218 --> 00:06:44.889
you're adding a 2Π.
 

00:06:44.889 --> 00:06:47.747
If you add capital T to
small t upstairs you're

00:06:47.747 --> 00:06:48.889
subtracting the 2Π.
 

00:06:48.889 --> 00:06:49.850
That doesn't matter.
 

00:06:49.850 --> 00:06:55.158
This shows you the periodicity
in space of λ and

00:06:55.158 --> 00:06:57.769
in time of capital T.
 

00:06:57.769 --> 00:07:00.461
You can also write
ω as

00:07:00.461 --> 00:07:03.232
2Π/T,
but 1/T is the

00:07:03.232 --> 00:07:04.310
frequency.
 

00:07:04.310 --> 00:07:06.718
This is what we normally think
of as frequency,

00:07:06.718 --> 00:07:08.759
so many hertz,
megahertz or whatever.

00:07:08.759 --> 00:07:09.980
That's the frequency.
 

00:07:09.980 --> 00:07:14.009
The angular frequency omega we
use is 2Π times that,

00:07:14.009 --> 00:07:17.266
because every time the thing
completes a cycle it goes by

00:07:17.266 --> 00:07:19.148
2Π,
and if it does f

00:07:19.148 --> 00:07:21.863
revolutions per second the
angular frequency is

00:07:21.863 --> 00:07:23.990
2Πf radians per
second.

00:07:23.990 --> 00:07:27.129
That's the difference between
revolutions per second and

00:07:27.129 --> 00:07:28.329
radians per second.
 

00:07:28.329 --> 00:07:33.202
Okay, so this is another way to
write it, and B will be

00:07:33.202 --> 00:07:34.560
the same thing.
 

00:07:34.560 --> 00:07:37.000
So you should understand what
this wave does.

00:07:37.000 --> 00:07:42.271
So imagine the plane wave is
coming from the blackboard

00:07:42.271 --> 00:07:43.639
towards you.
 

00:07:43.639 --> 00:07:45.946
If it's polarized this way--now
I should tell you what

00:07:45.946 --> 00:07:46.730
polarization is.
 

00:07:46.730 --> 00:07:49.870
Polarization is the direction
of E.

00:07:49.870 --> 00:07:52.504
B is understood to be
perpendicular to it,

00:07:52.504 --> 00:07:55.305
and the direction of
propagation is perpendicular to

00:07:55.305 --> 00:07:56.240
both of them.
 

00:07:56.240 --> 00:08:00.579
You can see E x B
is the direction of propagation

00:08:00.579 --> 00:08:01.560
of the wave.
 

00:08:01.560 --> 00:08:04.529
You do the cross product from
E to B and that's

00:08:04.529 --> 00:08:05.620
the way it advances.
 

00:08:05.620 --> 00:08:09.514
So what you will see is that if
these rows in this classroom

00:08:09.514 --> 00:08:11.855
were not curved,
but straight,

00:08:11.855 --> 00:08:16.536
then all the people in the
first row will see exactly the

00:08:16.536 --> 00:08:18.459
same electric field.
 

00:08:18.459 --> 00:08:21.028
So maybe it's pointing up.
 

00:08:21.028 --> 00:08:24.627
Then people in the second row
may see no electric field

00:08:24.627 --> 00:08:28.160
because they happen to be
sitting at that distance.

00:08:28.160 --> 00:08:32.639
People in the third row may see
a negative electric field.

00:08:32.639 --> 00:08:37.067
So every half-wave length it'll
go from 0 to maximum to 0 to

00:08:37.067 --> 00:08:40.443
minimum back to 0,
and so it oscillates at one

00:08:40.443 --> 00:08:41.120
time.
 

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:44.384
If you wait a little bit the
whole pattern will shift towards

00:08:44.384 --> 00:08:45.690
the back of the class.
 

00:08:45.690 --> 00:08:49.139
So what these guys saw now you
will saw a little later.

00:08:49.139 --> 00:08:50.399
How much later?
 

00:08:50.399 --> 00:08:54.019
It's the time light takes to go
from this row to your row.

00:08:54.019 --> 00:08:56.860
That's the delay,
ωt,

00:08:56.860 --> 00:09:03.660
in fact I told you,
you can write ky - ωt

00:09:03.660 --> 00:09:08.514
as--
let's see, as k times

00:09:08.514 --> 00:09:14.700
y - ct because
ω = kc.

00:09:14.700 --> 00:09:18.524
And I told you very early on
that any function of y - ct

00:09:18.524 --> 00:09:21.028
is a solution to wave
equation,

00:09:21.028 --> 00:09:24.499
and this tells you there's a
wave propagating to the right at

00:09:24.499 --> 00:09:27.440
speed c,
because whatever it does at one

00:09:27.440 --> 00:09:29.791
time,
say at t = 0,

00:09:29.791 --> 00:09:34.690
at later time it's shifted by
an amount ct.

00:09:34.690 --> 00:09:38.287
Now if I send an
electromagnetic wave towards

00:09:38.287 --> 00:09:40.913
you,
first thing you should notice

00:09:40.913 --> 00:09:44.740
is the electric field is
perpendicular to the plane,

00:09:44.740 --> 00:09:49.364
in which things are happening
are normal to the direction of

00:09:49.364 --> 00:09:51.644
propagation,
so the field vector is

00:09:51.644 --> 00:09:52.399
perpendicular.
 

00:09:52.399 --> 00:09:56.071
Both E and B are
in this plane and the wave is

00:09:56.071 --> 00:09:57.129
going that way.
 

00:09:57.129 --> 00:09:59.990
For this reason it's called a
transverse wave.

00:09:59.990 --> 00:10:05.312
So transverse means all the
action is in a plane

00:10:05.312 --> 00:10:08.710
perpendicular to the motion.
 

00:10:08.710 --> 00:10:13.100
So one example of transverse
waves is if you hold a string;

00:10:13.100 --> 00:10:16.116
I give it to the people in the
last row and I hold it and then

00:10:16.116 --> 00:10:16.759
I shake it.
 

00:10:16.759 --> 00:10:19.940
These ripples will go from me
towards the end of the room.

00:10:19.940 --> 00:10:23.779
The ripples are going like this
but the wave is going that way.

00:10:23.779 --> 00:10:25.778
That's a transverse wave.
 

00:10:25.778 --> 00:10:28.320
Or if I shake it this way,
same thing, it's going from

00:10:28.320 --> 00:10:29.038
side to side.
 

00:10:29.038 --> 00:10:32.250
The wave is going from me to
you.

00:10:32.250 --> 00:10:34.830
A longitudinal wave is a sound
wave.

00:10:34.830 --> 00:10:37.230
For example,
when I talk now some diaphragm

00:10:37.230 --> 00:10:40.320
in the throat pushes the air out
and compresses it,

00:10:40.320 --> 00:10:42.668
and maybe when it goes the
other way decompress it,

00:10:42.668 --> 00:10:45.168
and the motion of the air is
back and forth,

00:10:45.168 --> 00:10:47.820
namely in the same direction as
the propagation.

00:10:47.820 --> 00:10:49.633
So sound waves are
longitudinal,

00:10:49.633 --> 00:10:51.330
light waves are transverse.
 

00:10:51.330 --> 00:10:52.308
Yes?
 

00:10:52.308 --> 00:10:53.538
Student:  You said the
direction of

00:10:53.538 --> 00:10:56.250
E x B gives the
direction of propagation.

00:10:56.250 --> 00:10:59.940
Is there a significance to the
magnitude of that cross product?

00:10:59.940 --> 00:11:00.500
Prof: Yes.
 

00:11:00.500 --> 00:11:03.139
We'll come to that later today.
 

00:11:03.139 --> 00:11:03.960
That's correct.
 

00:11:03.960 --> 00:11:06.620
So E x B not only
tells you the direction it's

00:11:06.620 --> 00:11:08.966
reasonable to ask "If it is
a physical quantity,

00:11:08.966 --> 00:11:09.960
what does it mean?
 

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:15.460
And we'll find out shortly what
it means.

00:11:15.460 --> 00:11:19.628
Now polarization is the
direction of the electric field

00:11:19.628 --> 00:11:23.101
in the solution,
but we've got to realize that

00:11:23.101 --> 00:11:27.038
not every electric field has to
look like this.

00:11:27.038 --> 00:11:33.543
I can make a new problem where
I have solution looking like

00:11:33.543 --> 00:11:34.330
this.
 

00:11:34.330 --> 00:11:36.980
What is this guy doing?
 

00:11:36.980 --> 00:11:41.542
Can you tell it's going the
other way, because I just

00:11:41.542 --> 00:11:43.558
changed that to that.
 

00:11:43.558 --> 00:11:47.210
So that's the plane wave going
to the left.

00:11:47.210 --> 00:11:49.490
Now what should I do with the
B field?

00:11:49.490 --> 00:11:53.529
Its magnitude should be
E/c.

00:11:53.529 --> 00:11:56.392
I can also change this to going
backward, otherwise they don't

00:11:56.392 --> 00:11:57.048
form a pair.
 

00:11:57.048 --> 00:11:59.370
E and B have to
form a pair.

00:11:59.370 --> 00:12:02.350
But I claim this is not enough.
 

00:12:02.350 --> 00:12:04.668
If you took this pair it'll,
of course,

00:12:04.668 --> 00:12:07.538
satisfy the wave equation
because any function of y

00:12:07.538 --> 00:12:09.759
ct will satisfy the wave
equation,

00:12:09.759 --> 00:12:12.687
but I want you to remember
there are four Maxwell

00:12:12.687 --> 00:12:13.418
equations.
 

00:12:13.418 --> 00:12:15.200
You jiggle them all you get the
wave equation.

00:12:15.200 --> 00:12:17.149
It's just one consequence of
the four.

00:12:17.149 --> 00:12:20.551
You've got to satisfy all the
Maxwell equations,

00:12:20.551 --> 00:12:24.748
and some of them won't be happy
with this choice in which I

00:12:24.748 --> 00:12:26.918
reverse just the velocity.
 

00:12:26.918 --> 00:12:31.548
Can you think about what's the
way to fix that or what's wrong

00:12:31.548 --> 00:12:32.460
with that?
 

00:12:32.460 --> 00:12:35.514
I'm just saying that if the
wave traveled to the left

00:12:35.514 --> 00:12:38.629
instead of to the right that's
what I've done here.

00:12:38.629 --> 00:12:40.990
I would just reverse the
direction of propagation.

00:12:40.990 --> 00:12:42.549
That's not a good answer.
 

00:12:42.549 --> 00:12:44.750
Yes, you've got an answer?
 

00:12:44.750 --> 00:12:46.495
Student:  Does it have
to do with the fact that they're

00:12:46.495 --> 00:12:47.009
a cross product?
 

00:12:47.009 --> 00:12:48.639
Prof: Yeah,
so what's about the cross

00:12:48.639 --> 00:12:49.019
product?
 

00:12:49.019 --> 00:12:51.653
Student:  To make an
inverse cross product you have

00:12:51.653 --> 00:12:52.668
to make it negative.
 

00:12:52.668 --> 00:12:55.558
Prof: You want the cross
product to dictate the direction

00:12:55.558 --> 00:12:56.110
of motion.
 

00:12:56.110 --> 00:12:58.677
So if E and B are
like this the cross product

00:12:58.677 --> 00:12:59.428
